The `createWithUniqueName` function uses an unbounded `while (true)` loop that catches any `SQLiteConstraintException`. If a constraint other than the unique name constraint is violated (e.g., database corruption, schema mismatch, or nullability constraints), this loop will run infinitely, spinning the CPU and freezing the thread.

To prevent infinite loops, implement a retry limit (e.g., 10 attempts) and let the exception propagate if the limit is exceeded.

```kotlin
    private suspend fun createWithUniqueName(base: String, spec: KeyboardLayoutSpec): Long {
        repeat(10) {
            try {
                return repository.create(uniqueName(base), spec)
            } catch (_: SQLiteConstraintException) {
                // Name taken since the check; recompute against current rows.
            }
        }
        return repository.create(uniqueName(base), spec)
    }
```

